	<key>readme</key>
	<string>GAuth (Rust) — TOTP / 2FA codes in Alfred.

Setup:
1. Build the binary: `cargo build --release` in the gauth-rs repo. The bundled
   `gauth` binary is included by bundle.sh; if you move the workflow to another
   Mac, rebuild for that architecture.
2. (Optional) Configure a backend in ~/.config/gauth/config.toml. Defaults to the
   legacy ~/.gauth INI file. For MacPass, set backend = "macpass" and run
   `gauth associate` in a terminal once to approve the MacPassHTTP association.

Usage:
- Type `gauth` then (optionally) part of an account name.
- Press Enter on a result to paste its current 6-digit code at the cursor.

The selected code is copied as a transient clipboard item (not retained in
clipboard history) and auto-pasted at the cursor (requires Accessibility
permission for Alfred).

Note: the Script Filter passes the query via {query} substitution. If your Alfred
build expects argv instead, open the Script Filter and switch input to argv with
script `./gauth alfred "$1"`.</string>
